    #get-started.section.getting-started
      .container
        .row
          .col-xs-12
            %img.img-hand{alt: "Get Started", src: "assets/images/hand@2x.png"}/

        .row.what-is-dp
          .col-xs-12
            %h2.headline.text-center What Can I Do with Dogeparty?
            %p.text-center
              A lot, actually. Making your own token on Dogeparty means you can have your own asset to distribute, while
              still supporting the Dogecoin network and community. Raise funds in DOGE, and reward your supporters with
              a custom coin that can be tailored to your needs, without needing your own blockchain!

      %ul.container.about-dp
        %li.row
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.text-center
            %img.img-publish{alt: "Create", src: "assets/images/publish@2x.png"}/
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-8
            %h3.showable-toggle
              %span Create
              .toggle-icon.visible-xs
                %strong.plus +
                %strong.minus -
            %p.showable
              Want to publish a book or album without a publisher or have an amazing product ? Create your own token,
              put up a page explaining your goals and collect DOGE donations from your supporters!  You get the funds,
              your backers get a token that can give them access or  a share of the project. When you're ready,
              reward your backers by trading your work for the coin you gave out.
        %li.row
          .col-xs-12.text-center.visible-xs
            %img.img-tickets{alt: "Plan events", src: "assets/images/tickets@2x.png"}/
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-8
            %h3.showable-toggle
              %span Plan events
              .toggle-icon.visible-xs
                %strong.plus +
                %strong.minus -
            %p.showable
              Planning an actual DOGE Party, or even just a normal human event? Raise funds for the work and costs
              by selling an EVENT coin that can then be used at the event to pay for entry, drinks, and shibe snacks.
              You get the funds up front, and your guests get something tangible (and fungible) in return. This allows
              you to cover costs, and also give your backers a guaranteed unit of value beyond a name on the guestlist.
              In fact, the coin IS the guestlist!
          .col-sm-4.text-center.hidden-xs
            %img.img-tickets{alt: "Plan events", src: "assets/images/tickets@2x.png"}/
        %li.row
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-4.text-center
            %img.img-charity{alt: "Give back", src: "assets/images/charity@2x.png"}/
          .col-xs-12.col-sm-8
            %h3.showable-toggle
              %span Give back
              .toggle-icon.visible-xs
                %strong.plus +
                %strong.minus -
            %p.showable
              Raising funds for doing good?  Create a CharityCoin to give back to donors who support your cause.
              You can then make the token valuable by having businesses and supporters donate   and services which
              are auctioned for the CharityCoin at one-off or periodic events where only the CharityCoin is accepted.

